# Styling Guidelines

## Tailwind CSS

- Use utility classes for all styling
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use design tokens via CSS variables
- Avoid inline styles

```tsx
// ✅ Good
<div className="flex items-center gap-4 p-4 md:p-6 lg:p-8">

// ❌ Bad
<div style={{ display: 'flex', padding: '16px' }}>
```

## Responsive Design

```tsx
// Mobile first - base styles for mobile, then add breakpoints
<div className="
  flex flex-col        // Mobile
  md:flex-row          // Tablet
  lg:gap-8             // Desktop
">
```

## shadcn/ui Patterns

- Use the component's variant props
- Extend with className when needed
- Keep customizations minimal

```tsx
<Button variant="outline" size="lg" className="w-full">
  Submit
</Button>
```

## Dark Mode

- Use CSS variables for colors
- Always define both light and dark variants
- Test in both modes

```tsx
// ✅ Uses CSS variable that adapts to theme
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">

// ❌ Hardcoded color that won't adapt
<div className="bg-white text-black">
```

## Animation

- Use Tailwind's built-in animations
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Keep animations subtle

```tsx
<div className="animate-in fade-in duration-300 motion-reduce:animate-none">
```
